                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan reports that the former cabinet, consisting of four Liberals and two
                    Conservatives, remain in office, but that it is not believed that this
                    arrangement of the ministerial crisis will endure beyond the present year.</p>
            </div>
